  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving National Preparedness and Information Management for Ebola Virus Disease Surveillance at Ugandan Points of Entry</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM will support national efforts to strengthen capacity to implement the international health regulations to better prevent, detect and respond to the ebola virus disease (EVD) outbreak and other public health emergencies in Uganda at points of entries in Kisoro, Kanungu, Rubirizi and Rukungiri with a human mobility perspective. Specifically, IOM will support preparedness at points of entry (POEs) and will contribute to the overall coordination on surveillance under the leadership of the Ministry of Health and World Health Organization through a three-prolonged approach: improved targeting of national preparedness and public health response strategies with comprehensive population mobility-related information; enhanced national and local capacity at POEs to effectively prevent, detect and manage EVD through training for border and health personnel, screening and surveillance; and strengthened capacities to raise alerts and improve reaction to possible threats across the border through improved POE coordination.</narrative>
  </description>
